libscrypt
------------------------------------------
Linux scrypt shared library.

Full credit to algorithm designer and example code from Colin Percival here:
http://www.tarsnap.com/scrypt.html

Utilises BASE64 encoding library from ISC.

Official project page, including stable tarballs found here:
http://www.lolware.net/libscrypt.html

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.28-2
  libscrypt0-1.18-1bl1
  libssp0-4.8.2-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.23.52-5
  cygport-0.15.0-1
  gcc-core-4.8.2-3
  libtool-2.4.2-3
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/technion/libscrypt/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/technion/libscrypt/archive/v1.18.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libscrypt-1.18-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libscrypt-1.18-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libscrypt-1.18-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-1.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt0-1.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-devel-1.18-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libscrypt)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libscrypt.README
  /usr/share/doc/libscrypt/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libscrypt/README.md

(libscrypt0)
  /usr/bin/cygscrypt-0.dll

(libscrypt-devel)
  /usr/include/libscrypt.h
  /usr/lib/libscrypt.dll.a

